<div data-type="problem" id="fs-id2414002"><p id="fs-id2588389">The process in which antibodies attach to antigens, causing the formation of masses of linked cells, is called ________.</p>
<ol id="fs-id2573568" type="a">
<li>sensitization</li>
<li>coagulation</li>
<li>agglutination</li>
<li>hemolysis</li>
</ol>
</div>
<div data-type="solution" id="fs-id1548667" data-label="">
<p id="fs-id2834019">C</p>
</div>
</div>
<div data-type="exercise" id="fs-id1517312">
<div data-type="problem" id="fs-id2442960"><p id="fs-id2061794">People with ABO blood type O ________.</p>
<ol id="fs-id2583430" type="a">
<li>have both antigens A and B on their erythrocytes</li>
<li>lack both antigens A and B on their erythrocytes</li>
<li>have neither anti-A nor anti-B antibodies circulating in their blood plasma </li>
<li>are considered universal recipients</li>
</ol>
</div>
<div data-type="solution" id="fs-id1931352" data-label="">
<p id="fs-id2823045">B</p>
</div>
