<dl id="fs-id2733740"><dt>ABO blood group</dt> <dd id="fs-id2763985">blood-type classification based on the presence or absence of A and B glycoproteins on the erythrocyte membrane surface</dd></dl>
<dl id="fs-id2372415"><dt>agglutination</dt> <dd id="fs-id2575878">clustering of cells into masses linked by antibodies</dd></dl>
<dl id="fs-id811144"><dt>cross matching</dt> <dd id="fs-id2001493">blood test for identification of blood type using antibodies and small samples of blood</dd></dl>
<dl id="fs-id1488895"><dt>hemolysis</dt> <dd id="fs-id2759618">destruction (lysis) of erythrocytes and the release of their hemoglobin into circulation</dd></dl>
<dl id="fs-id2524132"><dt>hemolytic disease of the newborn (HDN)</dt> <dd id="fs-id2349123">(also, erythroblastosis fetalis) disorder causing agglutination and hemolysis in an Rh<sup>+</sup> fetus or newborn of an Rh<sup>&#8722;</sup> mother</dd></dl>
<dl id="fs-id1335568"><dt>Rh blood group</dt> <dd id="fs-id2363470">blood-type classification based on the presence or absence of the antigen Rh on the erythrocyte membrane surface</dd></dl>
<dl id="fs-id1339500"><dt>universal donor</dt> <dd id="fs-id2590692">individual with type O<sup>&#8722;</sup> blood</dd></dl>
<dl id="fs-id2593900"><dt>universal recipient</dt> <dd id="fs-id1472118">individual with type AB<sup>+</sup> blood</dd></dl>
